-- Japan's Yosano: Must keep Tokyo markets open after disaster
-- 
-- Mon Mar 14, 2011 9:33pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/03/15/us-japan-economy-yosano-idUSTRE72E0AH20110315

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japanese Economics Minister Kaoru Yosano said on Tuesday that it was important to keep the Tokyo markets open in the wake of a devastating earthquake and tsunami that rocked northeast Japan and triggered a nuclear power emergency north of Tokyo. 

 Closing the Tokyo market would have a major international impact, Yosano told a news conference after a cabinet meeting (Reporting by Kaori Kaneko; Editing by Edmund Klamann)